It was the moment millions of Broadchurch fans had waited almost two years for.

But the much-anticipated return of the ITV crime drama left many baffled – and not just by the plot.

Some who tuned in for the start of the second series on Monday night complained they struggled to understand actor David Tennant’s Scottish accent to the extent that they were forced to turn on the TV subtitles. 

